File: Eskom warns though that load-shedding can be implemented at short notice if there are shifts to in the system. JOHANNESBURG - Eskom says it will not be implementing load-shedding on Wednesday. The utility says it has made good progress in replenishing emergency services and that several of its units have been successfully returned. Eskom warns though that load-shedding can be implemented at short notice if there are shifts to in the system. READ: Cosatu eyes pension funds to rescue Eskom Consumers are being urged to continue to use electricity sparingly. Eskom has said it'll be load-shedding for the next 18-months as it conducts critical maintenance.